\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 57. T. nervosus} Gay ex Willk.,{\i  Suppl. Prodr. Fl. Hisp. }144 (1893). Like {\b 56}({\b d}) but leaves c. 6 × 1-1·5 mm, subcoriaceous, linear-spathulate, with distinct subparallel lateral veins and no marginal veins; calyx 3-4 mm, the tube about as long as upper lip. 2n = 28. •{\i  C. & E. Pyrenees; S.E. France} ({\i Mont Ventoux}). Ga Hs.
